ACCESSIBILITY COMMITMENT

This software is developed with the explicit intention of providing FREE and 
accessible tools for evidence documentation to all people, regardless of 
economic status. 

COMMERCIAL SALE IS EXPLICITLY PROHIBITED.

We especially encourage use by:
- Legal aid organizations serving low-income communities  
- Activists and journalists documenting social issues
- Researchers and academics in developing regions
- Individuals who cannot afford commercial documentation tools
- Nonprofit organizations serving vulnerable populations
- Pro bono legal practitioners
- Human rights organizations
- Community organizers and advocates

PERMITTED USES:
✅ Personal use for evidence documentation
✅ Educational use in schools and universities
✅ Nonprofit organizational use
✅ Legal aid and pro bono legal work
✅ Academic research and publication
✅ Journalism and investigative reporting
✅ Human rights documentation
✅ Community organizing and activism

PROHIBITED USES:
❌ Commercial sale of the software
❌ Commercial sale of derivatives or modifications  
❌ Incorporation into commercial products for sale
❌ Commercial licensing or distribution
❌ Any monetization of the software itself

CONTRIBUTIONS:
All contributions to this project automatically fall under this same 
non-commercial license. Contributors agree that their work will remain 
free and accessible to those who need it most.

The core principle: Evidence documentation tools should be FREE for everyone,
especially those who cannot afford expensive commercial alternatives.

For questions about usage or accessibility, please contact: accessibility@gitforensics.org